setCallback(RouteCallback<Route>) - Method in class me.ryanw.simplerouter.object.Route
Optionally, You can have a callback attached to a predefined route, which allows you to put code inside to be ran when the route URL is called.
setContext(Context) - Method in class me.ryanw.simplerouter.SimpleRouter
Sets the Context to be used when using Intents to launch new Activitys.
setParameters(Bundle) - Method in class me.ryanw.simplerouter.object.Route
Sets the parameters for this Route object, by breaking down the passed URL parameters and assigning them to the predefined route parameters, example; "/user/ryanw-se/projects/example" & "/user/:userId/projects/:projectId would assign the parameter userId the value ryanw-se and the projectId to the value example.
setTargetClass(Class<? extends Activity>) - Method in class me.ryanw.simplerouter.object.Route
Optionally, you can specify an Android activity to open when a predefined route is called.
